1. interview 2 people abbout task managers
	- note responses, observatiions, themes

- list situations where people struggled & what they need

- write job stories (4-6)
	- situation      (when i'm..)
	- motivation     (i want..)
	- outcome        (so i can..)
	- underlying need(because... ) 

	- evidence from interviews
	- inclusion risk
	- wcag (atlease 2)


2.  create pilot study tasks (2-5)
	- scenario (you've been asked to)
	- setup (pre pop list)
	- success criteria (participant uses, completed within)
	- metrics (time from page load to.., completed?, valid. errors, confidence )
	- accessibility checks (No-JS, keyboard only)
	- link to job stories(?)

3. define metrics
	- objective metrics (define,calc,reporting+eg.,split by)
	- subjective metrics(define,scale,collection method,reporting+eg)
	- accessibility metrics(define,measurement,reporting)

4. perform pilot study 
	- (consent process,set expectations)
	- "warm up"
	- read scenario, start timing, observe,
	- post tasks question (record confidence, notes, complete?)
	- debreif (what difficult,surprise,unsure, accessibility(if applic))
	- data recorded (metrics.csv) and manual in (pilot-notes.md)

5. week 10 analysis and fixes then interview again
